The paper deals with detection algorithms for spatial modulation in massive MIMO systems, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm for non-i.i.d. channel matrices, which could be categorized under statistical learning (cs.LG) or networked systems (cs.NI). The use of regularization techniques in the algorithm could also be relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of box-LASSO, which is a machine learning technique, and could be categorized under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
